{"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Some components can be used for "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"layouts"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Layouts","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"heading","text":"Colored Surface","anchor":"Colored-Surface","level":3},{"type":"tabNavigator","tabs":[{"title":"Orange","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_coloredSurface_Orange"}]}]},{"title":"Orange Inverse","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_coloredSurface_OrangeInverse","type":"image"}]}]},{"title":"Orange Business Tools","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_coloredSurface_OrangeBusinessTools","type":"image"}]}]},{"title":"Sosh","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_coloredSurface_Sosh","type":"image"}]}]},{"title":"Wireframe","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_coloredSurface_Wireframe"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Colored backgrounds use surface colors to maximize the contrast with content."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The colors of several OUDS components (for instance "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink"},{"type":"text","text":") are automatically adjusted if they are placed on "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To do so, some tokens associated with these specific colors can be customized and are identified with the "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Mono","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" suffix (for instance "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"buttonColorBgDefaultEnabledMono"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" of "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OrangeThemeButtonComponentTokensProvider","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"How it works","anchor":"How-it-works","level":4},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"According to the color, the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"text":" component adds in SwiftUI environment two flags:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"oudsUseMonochrome","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": to inform a component that needs to use mono version of tokens","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"oudsOnColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":": to inform a component it is placed on colored surface even if the mono is off"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","text":"How to use","anchor":"How-to-use","level":4},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ The folowing view has a colored background \"modeOnStatusPositiveEmphasized\" with","    \/\/ - a text with the color adapted according to the adjusted colorScheme      ","    \/\/ - a button that uses the mono version of tokens","","    \/\/ As view","    OUDSColoredSurface(color: theme.colorModes.modeOnStatusPositiveEmphasized) {","        VStack {","            Text(\"Status Positive Emphasized\")","            .oudsForegroundColor(theme.colors.colorContentDefault)","","            OUDSButton(text: \"Button\") {}","        }","    }","","    \/\/ As view modifier","","    VStack {","        Text(\"Status Positive Emphasized\")","        .oudsForegroundColor(theme.colors.colorContentDefault)","","        OUDSButton(text: \"Button\") {}","    }","    .oudsColoredSurface(theme.colorModes.modeOnStatusPositiveEmphasized)"]},{"type":"heading","text":"Debuging contrast ratios","anchor":"Debuging-contrast-ratios","level":4},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Some countries set up new laws so as to force companies to have a better accessibility of their digital services.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This is for example the case for France with the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/accessibilite.numerique.gouv.fr\/","type":"reference"},{"text":", also named “RGAA”.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The WCAG specifications, for AA level, defines a contrast ratio of 4.5:1 for textual elements (i.e. texts), and 3:1 for non-textual elements (i.e. link’s chevron)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However it is highly recommended for mobile devices to reach AAA level because of the screen sizes and luminosity issues, i.e. 7:1 for texts and 4.5:1 for non-textual elements."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Some components like ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink"},{"text":" can be used on ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSColoredSurface"},{"text":" ; thus in that case we can know the surface color for a given component on it, and compute the contrast ratio, and in the end display or not warnings.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To do that, some steps must be followed in your component implementation:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Rise the flag to allow debugging (e.g. i #DEBUG mode)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Get the environement variable defined by the colored surface containing the applied color"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the component implementation, add a line of code comparing the color to test and that surface"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Then keep an eye on your logs ; warnings will be added there if WCAG 2.1 3:1, 4.5:1 or 7:1 ratios are not reached, depending to the methods you call","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Rise the flag","#if DEBUG","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.oudsDebugWCAG21Colors = true","#endif","","\/\/ Supposing we are in your component View \/ ViewModifer struct","","\/\/ Get the applied surface color","@Environment(\\.oudsSurfaceColor) var surfaceColor","","\/\/ In the function defining the color to apply, add the line below","\/\/ where colorTokenToApply is the color to apply from a theme:","","\/\/ Non-textual components, in AA","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.debugContrastRatio(colorToApply, surfaceColor, .nonTextual)","","\/\/ Textual components and AAA to check","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.debugContrastRatio(colorToApply, surfaceColor, .AAA)"]},{"type":"heading","text":"Divider","anchor":"Divider","level":3},{"type":"heading","text":"How it works","anchor":"How-it-works","level":4},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A divider is used to separate content elements in a view. Two kinds of divider are proposed:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSHorizontalDivider","type":"reference"},{"text":": to separate elements stacked vertivally (VStask).","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSVerticalDivider","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":": to separate elements stacked Horizontally (HStask)."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A divider can be colored using color enumerated in the ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSDividerColor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Horizontal","anchor":"Horizontal","level":5},{"type":"tabNavigator","tabs":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_horizontalDivider_Orange","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"title":"Orange"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_horizontalDivider_OrangeInverse"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"title":"Orange Inverse"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_horizontalDivider_OrangeBusinessTools"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"title":"Orange Business Tools"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_horizontalDivider_Sosh"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"title":"Sosh"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_horizontalDivider_Wireframe"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"title":"Wireframe"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Vertical","anchor":"Vertical","level":5},{"type":"tabNavigator","tabs":[{"title":"Orange","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_verticalDivider_Orange"}]}]},{"title":"Orange Inverse","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_verticalDivider_OrangeInverse"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"title":"Orange Business Tools","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_verticalDivider_OrangeBusinessTools"}]}]},{"title":"Sosh","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_verticalDivider_Sosh","type":"image"}]}]},{"title":"Wireframe","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_verticalDivider_Wireframe","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"heading","text":"How to use","anchor":"How-to-use","level":4},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Add a vertical divider between items","HStack {","    Text(\"Hello wolrd!\")","    OUDSVerticalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","    Text(\"Happy to see you\")","}","","\/\/ Add an horizontal divider between items","VStack {","    Text(\"Hello wolrd!\")","    OUDSHorizontalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","    Text(\"Happy to see you\")","}"]}]}],"metadata":{"title":"Layouts","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"Components"}],"role":"article","images":[{"identifier":"ic_folder_categories.png","type":"icon"},{"identifier":"ic_folder_categories.png","type":"card"}]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/layouts"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://OUDSComponents/documentation/OUDSComponents/OUDSLink":{"kind":"symbol","title":"OUDSLink","role":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSLink"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" proposes layout with text only or text with icon."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It also proposes layout to navigate forward or backward. The link can be displayed in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"small"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"default"},{"type":"text","text":" size."}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSLink"}],"url":"\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudslink","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSCompon